  "doc_id": "32045",
  "text": "In general, coaches were addressing the content of the PD. However, they targeted the literacy domains unevenly. One way of interpreting this finding is that perhaps coaches unevenly targeted content areas because they were differentiating their coaching to meet the needs of individual educators. Indeed, this is one of the advantages of coaching as a PD tool, as it allows coaches to meet educators at their own developmental level and focus on what is most relevant for them and their practice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Rush & Sheldon, 2005) . Thus, in this study coaches may not have focused on instructional content areas that were already strong and instead focused on instructional content that they perceived as needs of the educators. This strategy has the potential to have positive impacts for educators and children.",
